.TH sigul_server_add_admin 1 "Jan 2009" sigul

.SH name
sigul_server_add_admin \- Add an administrator account to a signing server

.SH SYNOPSIS

\fBsigul_server_add_admin\fP [\fIOPTIONS\fP]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Adds a signing server administrator account to a signing server.
Prompts for the administrator acocunt name and password.

.SH OPTIONS

.TP
\fB\-c\fP, \fB\-\-config\-file\fP \fIPATH\fP
Use
.I PATH
as the per-user configuration file instead of \fB~/.sigul/server.conf\fR.

.TP
\fB\-v\fP, \fB\-\-verbose\fP
Be more verbose.
Using this option twice enables debugging output.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.B sigul_server_add_admin
returns with exit status 0 on success, non-zero on error.

.SH FILES
.TP
.B @configdir@/server.conf
A system-wide configuration file.

.TP
.B ~/.sigul/server.conf
A per-user configuration file.
Values defined in this file override the system-wide configuration file.

